<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB6EF75FDC3F95CFD63F8B8" box="[582,726,1769,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Microcentrum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB6EF75FDC3F95CFD63F8B8" box="[582,726,1769,1792]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Microcentrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB6EF75FD60F95DFC3AF8B8" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[741,911,1768,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropterinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phaneropterinae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB6EF75FC1FF95DFB92F8B8" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[922,1063,1768,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Microcentrini">Microcentrini</taxonomicName>
) from the ParNa Iguaçu. A and B: a syllable of the calling song of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB6EF75FE4CF8B8FDD2F89C" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[457,615,1804,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Microcentrum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolatum">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB6EF75FE4CF8B8FDD2F89C" box="[457,615,1804,1828]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">M. lanceolatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sonogram and spectrogram, respectively; C and D: a syllable of the calling song of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB6EF75FF36F884FEFAF8F0" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[179,335,1841,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Microcentrum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatum">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB6EF75FF36F884FEFAF8F0" box="[179,335,1841,1864]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">M. marginatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sonogram and spectrogram, respectively.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB6EF75FF42F8C3FE74F860" blockId="30.[151,1436,1910,2009]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB6EF75FF42F8C3FEEEF828" bold="true" box="[199,347,1910,1936]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFFB6EF75FEEBF8C3FE48F829" box="[366,509,1910,1937]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,185,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-29@30.[151,1436,181,1744]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Calling songs of species of Microcentrum (Phaneropterinae: Microcentrini) from the ParNa Iguaçu. A and B: a syllable of the calling song of M. lanceolatum, sonogram and spectrogram, respectively; C and D: a syllable of the calling song of M. marginatum, sonogram and spectrogram, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550087/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 14A, B</figureCitation>
): Males produce isolated syllables, only at night. Each syllable is composed by several pulses, in the beginning with slow intensity, followed by pulses in a crescendo intensity and after that with a decrescendo of intensity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FF22FDEEFF09" blockId="31.[199,785,151,285]" box="[199,603,151,177]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FF22FE1EFF09" box="[199,427,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 7.3 ± 1.9 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FF0EFE6EFF6D" blockId="31.[199,785,151,285]" box="[199,475,186,213]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FF0EFEF5FF6D" box="[199,320,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 5.9 ± 2 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FF6AFCA4FF41" blockId="31.[199,785,151,285]" box="[199,785,223,249]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FF6AFE9BFF40" box="[199,302,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Duration</emphasis>
: Pulse: 0.7 ± 0.07 ms; Syllable: 40 ± 2 ms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FEB6FD83FEA5" blockId="31.[199,785,151,285]" box="[199,566,258,285]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FEB6FEEAFEA5" box="[199,351,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Mute interval</emphasis>
: Pulse: 4.5 ± 1 ms.
</paragraph>
